
If you are using the Maven build system, you should use the "Test" suffix for test classes.
The Maven build system (via its surfire plug-in) automatically includes such classes in its test scope.


Difference b/w Mock and Spy: 
Mock : Create a mock object. Where you have to specify every thing
Spy : Uses some real method and some proxy method.

Mocking Framework:
Mockito, Easy Mock , Power Mockito

Mockito v/s Power Mockito:
Mockito does not provide any support to test private method and static method , but there is support for the same inside 
powerMockito.
